# âš™ï¸ Difference Between Blocking and Non-Blocking in Node.js (Hinglish)

Node.js me do tarah ke operations hote hain â€” **Blocking (Synchronous)** aur **Non-Blocking (Asynchronous)**.  
Chalo dono ko detail me samjhte hain ğŸ‘‡

---

## âš–ï¸ Table: Blocking vs Non-Blocking

| ğŸ”¹ **Basis** | ğŸ”¸ **Blocking (Synchronous)** | ğŸ”¸ **Non-Blocking (Asynchronous)** |
|--------------|------------------------------|------------------------------------|
| **Meaning** | Jab ek operation complete hone tak agla code **ruk jaata hai**. | Jab ek operation background me chalta hai aur agla code **continue** karta hai bina rukke. |
| **Execution Style** | Line-by-line, sequential execution. | Parallel style â€” ek task background me chalta hai, baaki code bhi execute hota rehta hai. |
| **Thread Usage** | Same thread wait karta hai jab tak task complete nahi hota. | Thread background me task bhej deta hai aur aage badh jaata hai. |
| **Performance** | Slow â€” kyunki ek time pe sirf ek hi kaam ho sakta hai. | Fast â€” multiple tasks ek saath handle hote hain. |
| **Example (Code)** | ```js<br>const fs = require("fs");<br>const data = fs.readFileSync("file.txt", "utf8");<br>console.log(data);<br>console.log("Next line");``` | ```js<br>const fs = require("fs");<br>fs.readFile("file.txt", "utf8", (err, data) => {<br>  console.log(data);<br>});<br>console.log("Next line");``` |
| **Output** | File read hone ke baad hi `"Next line"` print hoti hai. | `"Next line"` pehle print hoti hai, file ka data baad me print hota hai (jab ready hota hai). |
| **Blocking Behavior** | Main thread **block** ho jaata hai jab tak kaam complete nahi hota. | Main thread **free** rehta hai aur dusre kaam karta rehta hai. |
| **Use Case** | Small scripts ya one-time tasks jaha delay se farq nahi padta. | Real-time apps (Chat, APIs, servers) jaha speed aur concurrency zaroori hai. |
| **Example Output** | **Blocking:**<br>File Content<br>Next line | **Non-Blocking:**<br>Next line<br>File Content |
| **Node.js Default Nature** | Node.js me by default har operation **non-blocking** hota hai. | Blocking functions manually likhne padte hain (like `readFileSync()`). |

---

## ğŸ§  Example: Blocking (Synchronous)

```js
const fs = require('fs');

console.log("Start");
const data = fs.readFileSync('demo.txt', 'utf8');
console.log(data);
console.log("End");


EXample 
Socho ek restaurant me waiter (Node.js Event Loop):

Blocking: Waiter ek customer ke khatam hone ka intezaar karta hai.

Non-Blocking: Waiter ek order kitchen me deta hai aur next customer se order lene chala jaata hai.